content: improve. IBM z16 A01 core frequency is 5.2 GHz (same as IBM z15 T01), but with increased number of processors that share larger caches to have shorter access times and improved capacity and performance. Through innovative processor design (significant architecture changes, new cache structure, new Core-Nest interface, new branch prediction design that uses dense SRAM, and new on-chip AI accelerator for inference), the IBM Z processor performance continues to evolve. Enhancements were made on the processor unit design, including the following examples:  Cache structure  Branch prediction mechanism  Floating point unit  Divide engine scheduler  Load/Store Unit and Operand Store Compare (OSC)  Simultaneous multi-threading  Relative nest intensity (RNI) redesigns For more information about RNI, see 12.4, “Relative Nest Intensity” on page 479.
